{"aid": "http://arxiv.org/abs/2504.16785v1", "title": "Non collapse of the Sinha spectral sequence for knots in R^3", "summary": "We give an explicit description up to the third page of the Sinha homology
mod 2 spectral sequence for the space of long knots in $\mathbb{R}^3$, that is
conjecturally equivalent to the Vassiliev spectral sequence. The description
arises from a multicomplex structure on the Fox Neuwirth chain complexes for
euclidean configuration spaces. A computer assisted calculation reveals a non
trivial third page differential from a 2-dimensional class, in contrast to the
rational case.", "main_category": "math.AT", "categories": "math.AT,math.GT", "published": "2025-04-23T15:02:19Z"}
